casebody.data:
(October 22, 1953.)

(Republish.)

In the Matter of the City of New York, on Behalf of the New York City Housing Authority, Appellant-Respondent, Relative to Acquiring Title to Real Property Bounded by East 97th Street and Other Streets in the Borough of Manhattan, Selected as a Site for a Low-Rent Housing Project, Known as George Washington Houses. H. D. & W. Realty Corp. et al., Respondents-Appellants; Rose Tepper et al., Respondents.

Decree, so far as appealed from, unanimously affirmed, with one bill of $20 costs and disbursements to the respondents, and the order of this court, entered October 20, 1953 {ante, p. 865), vacated. No opinion. Present — Peck, P. J., Breitel, Bastow and Botein, JJ.
